Thanks, that is helpful. I can reproduce on master (and macOS).

Smaller example:
```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWriteCmd', {
  callback = function()
    vim.opt.modified = false
  end,
})
```

I haven't been able to reproduce this at all, but just looking at the backtrace the following patch might at least prevent the assertion:

```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/event/stream.c b/src/nvim/event/stream.c
index 17c1b0a07..e5592d9f7 100644
--- a/src/nvim/event/stream.c
+++ b/src/nvim/event/stream.c
@@ -128,15 +128,20 @@ void stream_may_close(Stream *stream)
 void stream_close_handle(Stream *stream)
   FUNC_ATTR_NONNULL_ALL
 {
+  uv_handle_t *handle = NULL;
   if (stream->uvstream) {
     if (uv_stream_get_write_queue_size(stream->uvstream) > 0) {
       WLOG("closed Stream (%p) with %zu unwritten bytes",
            (void *)stream,
            uv_stream_get_write_queue_size(stream->uvstream));
     }
-    uv_close((uv_handle_t *)stream->uvstream, close_cb);
+    handle = (uv_handle_t *)stream->uvstream;
   } else {
-    uv_close((uv_handle_t *)&stream->uv.idle, close_cb);
+    handle = (uv_handle_t *)&stream->uv.idle;
+  }
+
+  if (handle != NULL && !uv_is_closing(handle)) {
+    uv_close(handle, close_cb);
   }
 }
```

Really we should figure out why the handle is being closed more than once, but this would at least prevent a crash.

**EDIT:** Aha, I actually was able to reproduce this after rebuilding libuv in Debug mode. The patch above does indeed fix it.

This is the minimal reproduction:

```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWriteCmd', {
  callback = function()
    local id = vim.fn.jobstart('sleep 0')
    vim.fn.jobwait({id})
    vim.opt.modified = false
  end,
})
```

Both the `jobwait` and setting `'modified'` are required to reproduce.

This also works as a repro:

```lua
vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimLeavePre', {
  callback = function()
    local id = vim.fn.jobstart('sleep 0')
    vim.fn.jobwait({id})
  end,
})
```
